      <div class="alternatives-section">
        <h4>Alternative Activities</h4>
        <ul class="alternatives-list">
          <li><a href="https://secretlagoon.is/" target="_blank">Secret Lagoon</a>: Less crowded hot spring with facilities in the town of Fl√∫√∞ir.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.south.is/en/place/kerid-volcanic-crater" target="_blank">Keri√∞ Crater</a>: Volcanic crater lake with vibrant blue water and red volcanic rock.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.south.is/en/place/skalholt" target="_blank">Sk√°lholt Cathedral</a>: Historical site and former episcopal see, important in Icelandic history.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.solheimar.is/en" target="_blank">S√≥lheimar Eco-Village</a>: Iceland's first sustainable community.</li>
          <li><span class="gem">Tungna√°rfellsfoss Waterfall</span> - One of Iceland's widest waterfalls, yet rarely visited. Accessible via Road 208 with any vehicle in summer. This hidden gem offers the opportunity to experience a major waterfall without crowds.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="tip-box">
        Wear your swimsuit under your clothes for Reykjadalur to avoid changing in the open (there are limited changing facilities). Bring water shoes for comfort and a waterproof bag for electronics and valuables. The thermal river varies in temperature along its length - move upstream for warmer water.
      </div>
      
      <div class="notes-box">
        Stock up on groceries and gas in Selfoss, as it's the largest town in the region with better prices. Waterproof hiking boots are recommended for Reykjadalur, and hiking poles can be helpful on the sometimes slippery terrain. The trail can get crowded in summer afternoons - an early start is advantageous.
      </div>
