      <div class="highlights-section">
        <h4>Key Highlights of the Day</h4>
        <ul class="highlights-list">
          <li>Walking behind Seljalandsfoss Waterfall for a 360-degree perspective, a rare experience possible in very few waterfalls worldwide.</li>
          <li>The power and majesty of Sk√≥gafoss Waterfall, one of Iceland's largest and most photographed waterfalls, with mist that can be seen from kilometers away.</li>
          <li>The dramatic contrast of Vikurfjara Black Sand Beach where volcanic black sand meets powerful Atlantic waves beneath towering cliffs.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="accommodations-section">
        <h4>Accommodations</h4>
        <div class="accommodations-details">
          <strong>The Barn</strong>, Nor√∞urfoss. Double Room with shared bathroom. This rustic accommodation offers a tranquil countryside setting near V√≠k with mountain views and occasional Northern Lights sightings (though unlikely in July due to the midnight sun).
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="alternatives-section">
        <h4>Alternative Activities</h4>
        <ul class="alternatives-list">
          <li><a href="https://www.south.is/en/inspiration/nature/kvernufoss" target="_blank">Kvernufoss Waterfall</a>: Hidden gem near Sk√≥gafoss, requiring a short hike through a gorge. Far less crowded than its famous neighbor.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.south.is/en/inspiration/nature/solheimajokull-glacier" target="_blank">S√≥lheimaj√∂kull Glacier Viewpoint</a>: Accessible viewpoint of an outlet glacier from the massive M√Ωrdalsj√∂kull ice cap.</li>
          <li><span class="gem"><a href="https://epiciceland.net/thakgil-guide-best-hiking-trails/" target="_blank">Thakgil hiking area</a></span>: Beautiful canyons and green valleys surrounded by mountains, offering several hiking trails of varying difficulty.</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.vikhorseadventure.is/" target="_blank">Black Beach Horseback Riding</a>: Guided tours on Icelandic horses along the dramatic black sand beaches.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="tip-box">
        At Reynisfjara, <strong>never</strong> turn your back to the ocean. Sneaker waves are extremely dangerous and have claimed lives, even on seemingly calm days. Stay at least 20-30 meters from the shoreline and be ready to move quickly if necessary.
      </div>
      
      <div class="notes-box">
        Wear waterproof clothing for Seljalandsfoss, as you will get wet when walking behind it. Consider visiting Reynisfjara during off-peak hours (early morning or evening) for fewer crowds. The puffin viewing at Dyrh√≥laey is seasonal (May-August), and the site may have restricted access during nesting season.
      </div>
